development predecessor fairfield language technologies founded harrisonburg virginia usa  headquarters arlington virginia usa area served worldwide key people john hass ceo tom pierno cfo products rosetta stone language learning software rosetta stone kids reading software fit brains lexia learning tell me more software revenue  million  operating income  million  net income  million  total assets  million  total equity  million  owner abs capital partners northwest equity partners number of employees   website wwwrosettastonecom rosetta stone inc is an education technology software company that develops language literacy and brainfitness software best known for its languagelearning products in  the company expanded beyond language into educationtechnology with its acquisitions of livemocha lexia learning fit brains and tell me more contents  history  ipo  offices  endangered language communities  support for the combating online infringement and counterfeits act  awards  references  external links historyedit according to the company founder allen stoltzfus learned german through immersion while living in germany and found it relatively easy in the s stoltzfus began learning russian in a classroom setting but found the classroom setting much more difficult he wanted to simulate the german experience and he decided to use computer technology to create a similar learning experience he enlisted the aid of his brotherinlaw john fairfield who held a phd in computer science by  cdrom technology made the project possible they formed a company known as fairfield language technologies in harrisonburg virginia allen and john hired eugene stoltzfus allens brother greg keim and michael silverman they released their software product under the title the rosetta stone in  the company announced the hiring of tom adams a businessman with international experience as president and ceo in  the company changed names to rosetta stone ltd and converted from an s corporation to a c corporation ownership transferred to investment firms abs capital partners and northwest equity partners on september   rosetta stone inc filed an initial public offering with the securities and exchange commission on april   the company was listed as the rosetta stone on the new york stock exchange since  the companys president and ceo has been john hass rosetta stone is transitioning to a cloudbased business model that goes beyond language learning and deeper into education technology in  it acquired four companies—vivity labs inc creators of the fit brains trainer livemocha tell me more and lexia learning on september   rosetta stone announced the launch of a new kids division  and in november  it debuted its first kids reading program for consumers rosetta stone kids reading ipoedit on april   rosetta stone raised  million in its initial public offering of stock shares in its first full day of trading on the new york stock exchange the stock gained  from its opening price after a strong opening however the stock stumbled amid reports of weaknesses in rosetta stones us business resulting in the cancellation of a second offering and a disappointing year end price just  cents off its opening price the stock trades under ticker symbol rst as of december  the stock was at approximately  usd per share officesedit corporate headquarters are in arlington virginia there are also offices in harrisonburg virginia boulder colorado austin texas seattle washington bostonconcord massachusetts london united kingdom and seoul south korea endangered language communitiesedit in  rosetta stone ltd established its endangered language program to contract with endangered language communities interested in custom software development to support language revitalization efforts support for the combating online infringement and counterfeits actedit rosetta stone was among a group of companies signed to a letter supporting combating online infringement and counterfeits act coica a bill which opponents argue amounts to censorship awardsedit  tabby award  overall winner and users choice honoree in the android  education category rosetta course®  tabby award  users choice honoree in the ipad  education  adults professionals and general category rosetta course®  tabby award  overall winner and users choice honoree in the ipad  health  fitness category fit brains trainertm  academics choice smart media awards for rosetta course® for ios  academics choice smart media awards for rosetta stone® kids lingo letter soundstm  academics choice smart media awards for fit brainstm trainer  academics choice smart media awards for fit brains sparkys adventurestm  academics choice smart media awards for lexia reading® core®  best of elearning award of excellence for rosetta stone totale® pro for business solution  ikids awards for rosetta stone® kids lingo letter soundstm  eschool news readers choice award for lexia reading® core®prek reading program  stevie silver award for the best use of technology in customer service  stevie silver award for the young customer service professional of the year  stevie bronze award for customer service department of the year  stevie people’s choice for favorite customer service   eloqua markies award in the marketing and sales bff finalist  future  winner  technology cfo of the year  ceo tom adams named ernst  young entrepreneur of the year  ceo tom adams named ernst  young  entrepreneur of the year – retail  consumer products  mt top training and simulation companies  shenandoah valley technology councils high tech company award  stevie executive of the year award  deloittes technology fast award referencesedit  httpwwwbizjournalscomwashingtonblogtechflashrosettastonetobuyvivitylabshtml  httpwwwrosettastonecomleadership  rosetta stone to acquire fit brains creator vivity labs will enter fastgrowing braintraining market marketwatch retrieved  november    karsten strauss rosetta stone acquires livemocha and expands its reach in the cloud 